A driver of a lorry that was transporting maize flour has died after it rolled several times at Kinondo area along Ukunda-Msambweni road. Two other occupants sustained injuries while the body was taken to Msambweni Mortuary. Area OCPD Joseph Chebust said the lorry was coming from Diani headed for Msambweni town. Coast region has been experiencing heavy rains since Tuesday. The weatherman issued warned drivers to be keen on the roads. Click here for the latest political news 